The number of measles cases in your area is high right now.

Measles spreads easily and can lead to serious health problems, including:

* pneumonia
* meningitis
* blindness
* seizures (fits)

Having the MMRV vaccination is the best way to prevent measles. It also protects against mumps, rubella and chickenpox, or varicella.

2 doses of the MMRV vaccination gives lasting protection against all these illnesses.

[Find out more about the MMRV vaccine on NHS.UK](https://www.nhs.uk/vaccinations/mmrv-vaccine/)

## We’re offering catch-up vaccinations

If your child has had 2 doses of the MMR vaccine (the vaccination available before the introduction of MMRV), they will be fully vaccinated.

If your child has not had 2 doses of the MMR vaccine, we’d like your consent to vaccinate them with the MMRV vaccine at <%= location_name %> on <%= next_session_dates %>.

The vaccination is safe, quick and free.

If you’re not sure how many doses your child has had, having further doses will not cause any harm. If you’re sure your child has had 2 doses, please confirm this using the consent request form (the link is below).

Large international studies over the past 20 years have shown there is no link between the MMR vaccine and autism.

<%= talk_to_your_child_message %>

## How to respond

It’s important to let us know whether you do or do not want your child to have the vaccination. Do not reply to this email to tell us your decision. It will take less than 5 minutes to respond using the link below.

[Respond to the consent request now](<%= consent_link %>)

You need to respond by <%= consent_deadline %>.

If you do not respond, you’ll get automatic reminders. Responding will stop reminders.

If you cannot use the online form, you can respond over the phone using the contact details below. Replies to this email cannot be accepted as consent.

